description: The conclusion to the 7-part "Red Harvest." In the finale, all the threads of the past year converge into an explosive showdown. Tefe tries to rescue her foster parents, the Conways, from psychotic killer Romero. We discover the truth about Heather's father, Senator Strand. The secret identity of the DDI Director who's been trailing Tefe for a year is revealed. And the final fates of several members of the cast are decided. And finally, can the original Swamp Thing let all this go by without making an appearance?
name: Red Harvest Conclusion: Topiary

description: In this issue, two legends return: essential Swamp Thing artist John Totleben paints the cover, and the original Swamp Thing returns to confront Tef over her deeds. Tef counters him with an even more pointed question: If Swamp Thing is a god, why doesn't he try to end human suffering? In this emotional story, the true purpose of both Swamp Thing and Tef will be revealed.
name: Last of the Loose Ends

description: Tef's search for the Tree of Knowledge heats up! Journeying to Africa with Pilate, she meets an African medicine woman who agrees to take Tef to the Tree. But first Tef must atone for her past sins and ask permission from the continent's ancestors.

Final issue. This chapter in the legend of the Swamp Thing concludes in the search for the tree of life, as Tef learns the true story of the creation of the world. What will this revelation mean for the future of nature and humanity...and can Tef handle the truth?
The Sword of Damocles goes against his doppelganger, the hero know as Union. And after the battle only one will stand to hold the power of the Justice Stone.
name: Fire From Heaven - Finale, Part. 1
